cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.GR

The paper presents a framework for training sequential generative models to capture coordinated multi-agent trajectory behavior, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The framework also involves spatiotemporal modeling (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) to generate realistic multi-agent trajectories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of weak supervision (cs.SD) to train the models. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.CV, cs.GR, and cs.SD.
